FBIS4-54490 "dreeu084_i_94027" FBIS-EEU-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Croatian Official on `Demobilization' Intent Croatian Official on `Demobilization' Intent LD3004162894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 1500 GMT 30 Apr 94 LD3004162894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network English BFN [Text] Vladimir Soljic, defense minister in the government of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna, announced he will reduce the number of soldiers in the Croat Defense Council. Soljic explained there would be no demobilization in the usual meaning of the word because the war has not finished; rather, the superfluous soldiers will be deployed on working tasks.
